			<description><![CDATA[<p>
You love digital marketing and you are looking for a company that shares that passion. Here at 6S we live and breath digital marketing and have worked on 1000&#39;s of campaigns over the past 12 years. If your passion is to create and manage world class digital marketing campaigns...please read on.</p>
<p>
We are looking for candidates with two years experience or &nbsp;more managing successful digital marketing campaigns at an agency. We will be looking for examples of campaigns that you have created and run, and what resulted from those campaigns. We look for candidates with proven knowledge and skills in CPC, SEO, Google Analytics, email marketing and social media marketing.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>About 6S</strong></p>
<p>
6S is Western Canada&#39;s larget digital marketing company, and we continue to grow. While we love working hard, we also have fun - our culture is known to be one of the best in the industry. We have won numerious awards for being one the best companies to work for in BC. We value our team greatly and offer a work environment that is flexible and fun. Check our Facebook page, twitter, and blog, and if you think you would be a great fit, we would love to hear from you.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
2 years working at an agency in a digital marketing capacity</li>
<li>
In-depth knowledge of digital marketing implementation best practices</li>
<li>
In-depth knowledge of the Google AdWords platform</li>
<li>
At least 2 years of PPC, and SEO&nbsp;management experience</li>
<li>
At least 2 years experience working with Google Analytics</li>
<li>
Degree or Diploma or equivalent work experience</li>
<li>
Excellent presentation skills and comfortable speaking in client/project meetings</li>
<li>
Knowledge of some HTML and/or css</li>
<li>
Familar with content management systems like WordPress</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Duties</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Set up, optimize and maintain digital marketing accounts for clients, following best practices</li>
<li>
Communicate regularly with clients to ensure the highest level of customer satisfaction</li>
<li>
Communicate regularly with team members to ensure consistency of services within budgetary constraints</li>
<li>
Create monthly reports for clients that offer insights into initiatives undertaken by 6S marketing</li>
<li>
Develop strategies for clients that will help them reach their goals within the budgetary constraints</li>
<li>
Maintain knowledge of industry trends by regularly reading articles from industry leading websites such as SEOmoz, Search Engine Land, Search Engine Watch, ClickZ etc.</li>
<li>
Monitor client marketing initiatives on a weekly basis to ensure that the activities undertaken match the budget of the project and will help the client achieve their goals</li>
<li>
Review project initiatives and measure progress against goals</li>
<li>
Manage internal and external resources to ensure that campaigns are executed accurately, effectively, and within budget</li>
<li>
Proactively make strategic campaign recommendations to clients</li>
<li>
Generate and deliver performance reports to clients on an ongoing basis</li>
<li>
Manage client budgets to ensure proper allocation in accordance with campaign contract terms and project goals</li>
</ul>
<p>
Must be Vancouver (area) based. This is not a remote position.</p>
